ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: I feel like I have a choice in my actions
I am responsible for my own success
I know how to ask for help when I need it
1A. I always feel like I choose the things I do.
1B. I sometimes feel that its not really me choosing the things I do.
2A. My emotions sometimes seem alien to me.
2B. My emotions always seem to belong to me.
3A. I choose to do what I have to do.
3B. I do what I have to, but I do not feel like it is really my choice.
4A. I feel that I am rarely myself.
4B. I feel like I am always completely myself.
5A. I do what I do because it interests me.
5B. I do what I do because I have to.
6A. When I accomplish something, I often feel it was not really me who did it.
6B. When I accomplish something, I always feel it is me who did it.
7A. I am free to do whatever I decide to do.
7B. What I do is often not what I would choose to do.
8A. My body sometimes feels like a stranger to me.
8B. My body always feels like me.
9A. I feel pretty free to do whatever I choose to.
9B. I often do things that I do not choose to do.
10A. Sometimes I look into the mirror and see a stranger.
10B. When I look into the mirror I see myself.
